<H3> <TI>   Surplus Road Machinery From Sweden </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94EN0194Z Stockholm DAGENS NYHETER in Swedish 11 Jan 94 p 10 </F>
<F P=103> 94EN0194Z </F>
<F P=104>  Stockholm DAGENS NYHETER </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Swedish </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Road Machinery for Baltic States"] </F>
  [Text] (TT)--The government is recommending that the 
National Road Administration send surplus equipment to the 
Baltic states. 
  One result of that agency's reorganization was to make 
certain road machines and trucks superfluous. 
  The National Road Administration is selling off its surplus, 
but there is no demand for some of its older equipment. There is 
, however, a serious lack of that kind of equipment in the 
Baltic states. The government therefore considers it reasonable 
that the National Road Administration should send its unsalable 
older equipment over there. 

</TEXT>

