  Over the first 11 months of 1993, a greater volume of 
housing 
was commissioned than during the same period of the previous 
year in Armenia (by 27 percent) and Turkmenistan (by 4 percent); 
of general-education schools in Azerbaijan (by 3 percent), 
Armenia (by a factor of 2.6), Kyrgyzstan (by 68 percent), Russia 
(by 2 percent), and Uzbekistan (by 8 percent); of preschool 
institutions in Azerbaijan (by 35 percent) and Armenia (by 7 
percent); of hospitals in Belarus (by 18 percent), Russia (by 66 
percent), Turkmenistan (by a factor of 2.2), and Uzbekistan (by 
31 percent); of walk-in clinics in Azerbaijan (by a factor of 
4.2), Belarus (by 4 percent), and Turkmenistan (by a factor of 
4.3). 
