<F P=100> RUSSIA </F>
<F P=101> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Moscow Government Creates Guaranteed Import Credit Fund </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  944F0305A Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 25 Jan 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> 944F0305A </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [POSTFAKTUM report: "Credit Guarantee Fund Established"] </F>
  [Text] Aiming to ensure an uninterruptible supply of 
imported foodstuffs to Moscow in 1994, the capital city 
government has set up a credit guarantee fund for imports in the 
amount of 100 billion rubles [R]. Financing of deliveries will 
be done through special accounts that the Foreign Relations 
Department of the Government of Moscow will open in foreign 
banks. An agreement is expected to be reached with the Central 
Bank of Russia before 1 February on the matter of opening the 
guarantee fund's special accounts in foreign banks for a period 
of one year and transferring into them R100 billion in U.S. 
dollars at the Central Banks of Russia exchange rate. The 
Government of Moscow intends to give foreign banks the right to 
use the fund's deposit accounts as guaranteed collateral for 
1994 purchases and deliveries to Moscow of foodstuffs and food 
processing equipment. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

